##Italy's emergency lockdown

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Nan Boyi, _ the_paper _ reporter

To stem the spread of the new coronavirus, Italy on March 8 sealed off Lombardy 见 Lombardia，Reg. And 11 neighbouring provinces in the north of the country, affecting the free movement of 16M people until April 3.

"We face an emergency, a national emergency, " Italian Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte announced at a 2 a.m. news conference, The New York Times reported on March 8, a decree to curb the spread of the disease took effect on March 8.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The draft Italian government decree, obtained by The Wall Street Journal on July 7, said the country would impose sweeping restrictions on northern Lombardy 见 Lombardia，Reg. And 11 neighboring provinces, the restrictions will affect a quarter of Italy's population. People in these areas should "absolutely avoid any activity entering or leaving the area, " the decree said, and should only be allowed to move within the affected area if there are "non-deferrable" commercial or health concerns.

Reported that the short-term equivalent to the sacrifice of the Italian economy, Italy, before the outbreak of a number of towns have been closed measures. The new law will further transform the wealthy northern region of Italy into a red zone of quarantine until at least April 3rd, covering such landmarks as the economic and Cultural Capital of Milan and Venice.

In addition, funerals and cultural events will be banned in these areas, swimming pools will be closed and medical workers'leave will be cancelled. The law also requires bars and restaurants to keep customers at least a metre apart or they will be forced to close. Both the police and the military will be present to ensure that the law is enforced, and violators could be fined or jailed, according to the Wall Street Journal.

Italy is already the worst affected country in Europe. The Italian government has ordered the closure of schools, universities, cinemas and theaters and other public places.

On March 7th Nicola Zingaretti, the leader of Italy's ruling coalition, confirmed that he had tested positive for the new coronavirus. Alberto Sirio, president of Italy's Piedmont region, became the country's second regional president in 24 hours to be diagnosed with new pneumonia.

The Associated Press reported Thursday that a coronavirus outbreak is hitting Italy's already shaky economy. The Wall Street Journal also said Italy's tourism and luxury goods industries had been hit hard and that the impending blockade would only make matters worse.

According to the latest data released by the Italian Ministry of Health at 18:00 local time on March 8, there are 6,387 cases of new coronavirus in Italy, 366 deaths and 622 cured cases, bringing the total number of confirmed new coronavirus infections to 7,375, there were 1492 new cases and 133 new deaths compared with 18:00 on March 7.

According to Italian media reports, the Italian Chief of the Army Staff Falliner 8 afternoon statement said he tested positive for the virus nucleic acid, is now in his residence isolation. In accordance with government decrees and relevant health regulations, he is cooperating in the investigation of his movements and exposure history in recent days. Falliner said in a statement that he would continue to carry out his duties, but that the duties requiring his presence would be replaced by another general. He paid tribute to the army men and women who are fighting the epidemic and thanked them.
